Honestly Frank..we may agree to some extent on this. This borders on
principles of magick, and using your Will to effect change in the universe.
It is kinda like where magick and science meet.

Buddhism has beliefs along these lines as well, though they do not explain
it quite like this. They believe there is an objective universe, but that we
project our own images onto this matter, thereby perceiving things
differently. They believe we percieve matter mainly based on our emotions,
and what we think want versus what is actually there. Part of achieving
enlightenment is actually breaking out of the emotional way of viewing
things, and actually using our minds to our advantage, rather then just
letting our emotions rule what we perceive.

